    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-01-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-01-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="2"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d2">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/3107</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-01-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 4, 1917</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received January 5, 9.43
                        p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>771. Noon press report confirmed that British and French Prime Ministers, French
                    War and Munition Ministers, and <persName corresp="#p_RGSWR1">General
                        Robertson</persName>, Lord <persName corresp="#p_MSA1">Milner</persName>,
                    and Russian General Palitsyn will arrive Rome to-morrow, Friday morning.
                        <persName corresp="#p_CGL1">General Cadorna</persName> also here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PTN1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
